The paper deals with the collective evolution of weights in large-width neural-network-like models, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of stationary points and convergence rates, which are topics related to numerical analysis and optimization, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior of the transport equation in different scenarios, which could be relevant to the study of complex systems (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
